\begin_layout Subsection
Discussion
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This section was about the idea of managing cutting planes, and as a byproduct
 we get an accelerated rate of convergence.
 As we will see later, standard accelerated gradient descent does not use
 line search and achieves the rate 
\begin_inset Formula $1-\sqrt{\frac{\mu}{L}}$
\end_inset

.
 However, it seems that the use of line search helps in practice and that
 with a careful implementation, line search can be as cheap as gradient
 computation.
 For more difficult problems, one may want to store multiple quadratic lower
 bounds (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "drusvyatskiy2016optimal"
literal "true"

\end_inset

).
